meanings.definition: To browse excessively or too much.
meanings.sent1: The deer overbrowsed the field, eating all the grass.
meanings.sent2: She overbrowsed the internet for hours, looking for the perfect gift.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel overbrowsed the nut stash, leaving nothing for winter.
meanings.sent4: His curiosity overbrowsed every book in the library, seeking answers.
meanings.sent5: The student overbrowsed the textbook, trying to absorb all the information.

meanings.sent1: The overbrowsed book had torn pages and a worn cover.
meanings.sent2: The overbrowsed website crashed due to high traffic.
meanings.sent3: The overbrowsed trail was now muddy and trampled.
meanings.sent4: The overbrowsed garden showed signs of wilting plants.
meanings.sent5: The overbrowsed magazine had pages falling out from frequent reading.
